================================================================================
K2 Plus phone-home proof. mitmproxy capture, redacted for public release.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source proxy log : /home/obsidian/captures/mitm/api_crealitycloud.log
Source SHA-256   : (recorded separately; see provenance section)
Capture endpoint : mitmproxy intercepting outbound 443 from printer LAN segment
Window           : 2026-05-30 (continuous, multi-hour)
What this shows  : Printer initiates outbound TLS to api.crealitycloud.com and
                   devdata.cxswyjy.com on its own. Every connection presents a
                   __CXY_JWTOKEN_ JWT in request headers, alongside
                   __CXY_DUID_ (cloud device serial), __CXY_UID_ (Creality
                   account UID), brand/OS/app fingerprint headers, and a fresh
                   request ID. JWT bodies decoded during analysis carried:
                       sub = <device serial>
                       aud = <Creality account UID>
                       iss = https://api.crealitycloud.com
                       exp = unix timestamp (multi-week validity)
                   This is a fully authenticated cloud session held open by the
                   printer despite the operator having refused the Cloud Terms
                   of Service. Endpoints observed include:
                       POST /api/cxy/v2/firmware/checkUpgrade
                       POST /api/cxy/v2/slice/profile/official/material/printerParameter
                   plus the ongoing churn against api.crealitycloud.com and
                   devdata.cxswyjy.com on every loop.
Redaction policy : The following values are replaced wherever they appear:
                       LAN IP                  -> [REDACTED_LAN]
                       Cloud device serial     -> [REDACTED_DEVICE_SERIAL]
                       Creality account UID    -> [REDACTED_ACCOUNT_UID]
                       JWT bearer token        -> [REDACTED_JWT]
                       __CXY_REQUESTID_ values -> [REDACTED_REQID]
                       Cloudflare __cf_bm      -> [REDACTED_CF_BM]
                       Cloudflare CF-RAY       -> [REDACTED_CF_RAY]
                   All endpoint paths, header NAMES, HTTP methods, response
                   codes, mitmproxy connect/disconnect events, ephemeral source
                   ports, destination FQDNs and IPv6 addrs are preserved.
